 <H1>And the Bad Part�</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>All these extensions had to be part of the base protocol

</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Have blurred the (already implicit) line between base protocol and extensions in HTTP

</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Cost has been a very complex protocol

</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>HTTP/1.1 has been under way a long time

<LI>Not just result of complex extensions but how they interact

<LI>Adding new features gets harder and harder

</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Reason: No way of replacing existing features

</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Cost of backwards compatibility keeps increasing

<LI>Will never be able to replace existing features</UL></UL></P>

